en_680821_0	In order to promote and enhance age-old self-defence techniques, physical strength, endurance, courage and tolerance among the soldiers, Major General Niyshshanka Ranawana, Commander, Security Forces – Kilinochchi (SF-KLN) who is also the Chairperson, Sri Lanka Army Angampora Committee introduced a session of Angampora training for Army personnel serving under the Security Force Headquarters - Kilinochchi (SFHQ-KLN) as an initial programme.
en_680821_1	Afterwards, Sri Lanka Army Angampora Committee initiated a month-long ‘Angampora’ training course under the supervision of experts in the field.
en_680821_2	The opening ceremony of the training module began recently at the Nelumpiyasa auditorium in the presence of the Commander, Security Forces - Kilinochchi (SF-KLN), Major General Niyshshanka Ranawana who graced as the Chief Guest, along with the General Officer Commanding, 65 Division, Brigade Commanders, senior Officers and Officers.
en_680821_3	Ritigala Sinhakara Parapure Kalakeerthi Kalavibushana Mr. Dewinda Laksiri Ranasinghe and his team voluntarily participate in the entire period to conduct the programme.
en_680821_4	100 male Army personnel in under command battalions are currently participating in the training programme.
